<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-06-23T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-06-23T18:00:00-05:00" n="715" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d715">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">823.51/1282: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-06-23T19:00:00-04:00">June 23,
                                    1939—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>40. Please report by telegraph whether you have conveyed to President
                            Benavides the substance of the Department’s telegram no. 39, June 13, 1
                            p.m. and whether he understands that there must be a most careful and
                            thorough preliminary exploration of the possibilities before a Peruvian
                            mission is sent to Washington.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>